title="Abstract Algebra">Abstract Algebra</fr:link> Section 0.2</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a,b\in \mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex> are nonzero integers, there exists a unique positive integer called the <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Greatest Common Divisor</html:dfn> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex>, usually denoted <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\gcd (a,b)]]></fr:tex>, such that:</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\gcd (a,b)\mathrel {\bigm |} a]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\gcd (a,b)\mathrel {\bigm |} b]]></fr:tex> (so <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\gcd (a,b)]]></fr:tex> is a common divisor of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex>)</fr:li>
<fr:li>if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e\mathrel {\bigm |} a]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e\mathrel {\bigm |} b]]></fr:tex> is another integer, then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e\mathrel {\bigm |}\gcd (a,b)]]></fr:tex> (so <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\gcd (a,b)]]></fr:tex> is the <fr:em>greatest</fr:em> such divisor).</fr:li></fr:ol><fr:p>If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\gcd (a,b)=1]]></fr:tex> we say <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> and {b} are <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Coprime</html:dfn> (or are <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Relatively Prime</html:dfn>).</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
