type="local"
href="nst-0011.xml"
addr="nst-0011"
title="Equivalence relation">Equivalence relation</fr:link> on the integers by
<fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\sim  b\iff  n\mathrel {\bigm |}(b-a).]]></fr:tex>
This is reflexive (<fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\sim  a]]></fr:tex> since <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n\mathrel {\bigm |}(a-a)]]></fr:tex>), symmetric (<fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\sim  b\iff  n\mathrel {\bigm |}(b-a)\iff  n\mathrel {\bigm |}(a-b)\iff  b\sim  a]]></fr:tex>) and transitive.</fr:p><fr:p>Then the quotient set <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {Z} /\mathord {\sim }]]></fr:tex> is often denoted <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {Z} / n\mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex>. Moreover, there are well-defined operations <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[[a]+[b]=[a+b]]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[[a]\cdot [b]=[a\cdot  b]]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
